<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1380" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1380">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/221.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Spanish Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-10">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: I beg to
                                acknowledge the receipt of your note of April 9, in regard to the
                                expulsion of Spanish subjects from Torreon, and in reply to inform
                                you that the Department is in receipt of a telegram from its
                                representative at El Paso, Texas, dated April 9, in which it is
                                stated that General Venustiano Carranza undoubtedly gave to the
                                press the statement attributed to him in yesterday’s newspapers to
                                the effect that the property of Spaniards expelled from Torreon
                                would not be confiscated.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>